	<div id="content">
		<h1>Why am I here?</h1>
		
		<p>
			We are <a href="http://www.adestra.com/">Adestra</a>. We provide
			<b>email newsletter and marketing services</b> to a variety of
			clients around the world. This site is used to host images, pages
			and other services used in emails that our clients send using our
			platform.
		</p>

		<p>
			Normally, email recipients shouldn't see this page, but there are
			several reasons why you might have ended up here:
		</p>
		
		<h3>Broken link in email</h3>
		<p>
			If you have come here from a link in an email, that link may be
			broken. Please try copying the link out of the original email and
			pasting into your browser's address bar.
		</p>
		
		<h3>Unsubscribe from a mailing list</h3>
		<p>
			If you are attempting to unsubscribe from a mailing sent by one of
			our clients using our system, then the quickest method is clicking
			the 'unsubscribe' link in the email you were sent; they should all
			contain one, and they do work.
		</p>
		
		<h3>Received an email in error</h3>
		<p>
			If you feel you have been sent an email in error, or you have
			experienced problems unsubscribing, please contact our Abuse team
			at <a href="mailto:abuse@adestra.com">abuse@adestra.com</a>. They
			will investigate your issue and ensure it is addressed.
		</p>
		
		<h3>Questions, complaints or any other concerns</h3>
		<p>
			If you have any questions or comments regarding our services, you
			can contact us via the
			<a href="http://www.adestra.com/contact-us/">contact page on our website</a>.
		</p>
		<p>
			If you wish to make a complaint, or have any questions or comments
			regarding a specific email we have sent, please feel free to contact
			our Abuse team at <a href="mailto:abuse@adestra.com">abuse@adestra.com</a>.
			It may help us if you can forward or attach a copy of the email that
			you have received.
		</p>
